## Metadata Upsertion [/rest/metadata/{entityReferenceType}/{referenceUrn}]
### Add metadata for a specific entity [PUT]

Inserts a new key-value or updates an existing key value related to the specified entity. This endpoint uses an **upsert** algorithm, inserting the metadata record(s) if the named key doesn't already exist, or
updating the values (and only the values) in the metadata record if the key already exists.

This endpoint expects the submission of a JSON array. The design allows for the rapid definition of multiple metadata
key-value pairs in a single operation. Each array entry must include a `key`, `dataType`, and a `rawValue` field.

> Metadata values are restricted to no more than 4K in size. Instead, large values should use a file instead of metadata.

+ Parameters
    + entityReferenceType: `Object` (required, EntityReferenceType) - Valid EntityReferenceType enum value
    + referenceUrn: `aa1ebdfa-d428-4d31-8740-858e6b65a385` (required, string) - Case-sensitive `urn` (`objectUrn` works also, if entityReferenceType is `Object`) of an existing entity of type `entityReferenceType`

